{"title": "Life of Philip Melanchthon", "description": "Philip Melanchthon  (1497 \u2013 1560) is best known as the theologian of the Protestant Reformation, systematizing and defending much of Martin Luther\u2019s works and creating an educational system based on them.  He was instrumental in the writing of the Augsburg Confession, the most influential document of the Reformation.  Melanchthon and Luther, of different temperaments, did not always agree but respected each other and became a formidable spearhead for the Reformation.  \nKarl Ledderhose here provides a comprehensive biography of Melanchthon including his principle ideas and activities, so it also serves as a history of many important aspects of the Reformation.\n - Summary by Larry Wilson", "duration": 45136, "language": "English", "authors": [{"id": "14787", "name": "Karl Friedrich Ledderhose"}], "coverArt": null, "copyright_year": "1855", "genres": ["Biography & Autobiography"], "supporters": [{"role": "Read by", "name": "LibriVox Volunteers"}, {"role": "Book Coordinator", "name": "Larry Wilson"}, {"role": "Meta Coordinator", "name": "Kristine Bekere"}, {"role": "Proof Listener", "name": "Larry Wilson"}], "sections": [{"section": 0, "title": "Prefaces", "readers": [8425], "path": "https://www.archive.org/download/philip_melanchthon_2103_librivox/melanchthon_00_ledderhose_64kb.mp3", "duration": 412}, {"section": 1, "title": "His Youth", "readers": [12963], "path": "https://www.archive.org/download/philip_melanchthon_2103_librivox/melanchthon_01_ledderhose_64kb.mp3", "duration": 990}, {"section": 2, "title": "The University", "readers": [13967], "path": "https://www.archive.org/download/philip_melanchthon_2103_librivox/melanchthon_02_ledderhose_64kb.mp3", "duration": 751}, {"section": 3, "title": "His Debut in Wittenberg, and at the Leipzig Disputation", "readers": [13863], "path": "https://www.archive.org/download/philip_melanchthon_2103_librivox/melanchthon_03_ledderhose_64kb.mp3", "duration": 706}, 